 Hence, setting 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha =-3/32$
\end_inset 

 in equation 
\begin_inset LatexCommand \ref{upcomingrichardson}

\end_inset 

, we get 
\begin_inset Formula \[
y_{j+1,4r+2}=p_{4}\left(x_{j,2r+1}\right)-\frac{105\alpha +9(1-\alpha )}{2^{4j}}a_{4}=p_{4}\left(x_{j+1,4r+2}\right)\]

\end_inset 

since for 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha =-3/32$
\end_inset 

, 
\begin_inset Formula $105\alpha +9(1-\alpha )=0$
\end_inset 

.
 Therefore, the HRS scheme with 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha =-3/32$
\end_inset 

 reproduces quartic polynomials.
 
