Given that the algorithm converges to continuous functions and is local,
 we can easily prove that it must be 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset 

stable
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset 

.
 In general terms, an algorithm 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset 

 is said to be stable if for any data 
\begin_inset Formula $z$
\end_inset 

, 
\begin_inset Formula $|R(z+\delta z)-R(z)|\leq K|\delta z|$
\end_inset 

 
\begin_inset LatexCommand \cite{KuDa}

\end_inset 

.
\layout Corollary

For 
\begin_inset Formula $-25/56<\alpha <15/32$
\end_inset 

, the HRS schemes (algorithm 
\begin_inset LatexCommand \ref{4pointhrssalgo}

\end_inset 

) are stable, that is, given 
\begin_inset Formula $\left|z_{j,k}-\widetilde{z}_{j,k}\right|<\delta \, \forall k\in \Z $
\end_inset 

 then 
\begin_inset Formula $\left|z_{j+n,k}-\widetilde{z}_{j+n,k}\right|<K\delta \, \forall k\in \Z $
\end_inset 

 for all integers 
\begin_inset Formula $n>0$
\end_inset 

 and a constant 
\begin_inset Formula $K$
\end_inset 

 independent of 
\begin_inset Formula $\delta $
\end_inset 

.
\layout Proof

Assume we use any 
\begin_inset Formula $4-$
\end_inset 

point subdivision scheme as an initialization step on the initial data on
 
\begin_inset Formula $z_{j,k},\widetilde{z}_{j,k}$
\end_inset 

.
 For 
\begin_inset Formula $-25/56<\alpha <15/32$
\end_inset 

, by theorem 
\begin_inset LatexCommand \ref{maintheorem}

\end_inset 

, given the initial data 
\begin_inset Formula $y_{j,k}=\delta _{k,0}\, \forall k\in \Z $
\end_inset 

, we get a continuous (
\begin_inset Formula $C^{1}$
\end_inset 

) interpolation function 
\begin_inset Formula $F(x)$
\end_inset 

.
 Let 
\begin_inset Formula $M=\left\Vert F\right\Vert _{L^{\infty }}$
\end_inset 

, assume 
\begin_inset Formula $\left|z_{j,k}-\widetilde{z}_{j,k}\right|<\delta \, \forall k\in \Z $
\end_inset 

, by linearity, the interpolation function of 
\begin_inset Formula $z_{j,k}-\widetilde{z}_{j,k}$
\end_inset 

 is given by 
\begin_inset Formula $f(x)=\sum _{k=-\infty }^{\infty }\left(z_{j,k}-\widetilde{z}_{j,k}\right)F_{j}\left(x-x_{j,k}\right)$
\end_inset 

 but since 
\begin_inset Formula $F$
\end_inset 

 has compact support 
\begin_inset Formula $[x_{j,-3},x_{j,3}]$
\end_inset 

 then 
\begin_inset Formula $\left\Vert f\right\Vert _{L^{\infty }}\leq 6M\delta $
\end_inset 

.
 It means that the values of the stable nodes are bounded by 
\begin_inset Formula $-6M\delta $
\end_inset 

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $6M\delta $
\end_inset 

.
 The placeholders must also be bounded by 
\begin_inset Formula $6M\delta \sum _{k\in \Z }\left|\gamma _{4k-1}^{DD4}\right|$
\end_inset 

(see equation 
\begin_inset LatexCommand \ref{hrswidguess}

\end_inset 

).
